# ABOUTME: Template for relayer-v2/compose/secrets.env (gitignored; spec §11.1). Copy to
# ABOUTME: secrets.env and fill in. NEVER commit the real file — the pre-commit hook blocks it.
# cp secrets.env.example secrets.env

# Actor keys (D2: these reach ONLY the actor container).
RELAYER_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...
RELAYER_RAILGUN_MNEMONIC="word1 word2 ... word12"
# Optional: assert the derived 0zk address matches (boot-fails on mismatch, §6.5).
#BROADCASTER_RAILGUN_ADDRESS=0zk1...

# Database passwords (compose env-file layering overrides the committed placeholders).
#POSTGRES_PASSWORD=...
#WATCHER_DB_PASSWORD=...
#ACTOR_DB_PASSWORD=...

# RPC provider lists — the ONLY place RPC URLs are set for sepolia/mainnet (§11.1; the
# committed env files intentionally omit them). Comma-separated: the watcher load-balances
# across every URL (more free-tier throughput for backfills); the actor uses only the FIRST
# entry, so put the provider you trust most for transaction submission first. URLs with
# embedded keys are secrets and belong here, never in a committed file.
# Sepolia (keyless public defaults; prepend keyed URLs, e.g. https://eth-sepolia.g.alchemy.com/v2/KEY):
HUB_RPC=https://ethereum-sepolia-rpc.publicnode.com
CLIENT_A_RPC=https://base-sepolia-rpc.publicnode.com
CLIENT_B_RPC=https://arbitrum-sepolia-rpc.publicnode.com
# Mainnet (replace the sepolia values above when deploying NETWORK=mainnet):
#HUB_RPC=https://ethereum-rpc.publicnode.com
#CLIENT_A_RPC=https://base-rpc.publicnode.com
#CLIENT_B_RPC=https://arbitrum-one-rpc.publicnode.com
